property.name: block_radius
property.help: ISSUE: 60 will lag about 40s on my machine. it will NOT create the intended meteorite crater. It will NOT disintegrate the blocks so they will spawn as falling terrain and will be very laggy. Also, the explosion is like a ray cast that only hit surfaces, so the teleport action is required to reach the max range possible. If the player was below the ground level, it would only hit a few blocks around nearby.

action_sequence.name: eventGSKDeusExDeathExplosionAlt
action_sequence.help: this crater workaround is very laggy. The X Z teleport slight positioning is to try to prevent creating bridges right below the player. The increasing Y is to try to avoid a hole in the center. 8 explosions is to try to make it look more spheric by exploding the same places many times. The delays are meant to try to make it easier on the CPU and should be removed if they become unnecessary on new engine versions. TODOA: this should instead happen where the DeusEx died. This should just pierce blocks and disintegrate them (w/o falling terrain) to be much faster.
